    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style and culture of modern Jordan. Following the dissolution of the Ottoman Empire, Britain created this semi-autonomous region of Transjordon in the early 1920s, which gained its independence in 1946 and was named Jordon in 1950.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
